<subSubSection pageId="52" pageNumber="53" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="52.[151,1436,1446,1509]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,287,1446,1472]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Verrill" authorityYear="1899" box="[298,435,1447,1472]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Litonotaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[298,435,1447,1472]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Litonotaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is unusual for the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Forbes" authorityYear="1841" box="[658,814,1447,1473]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="family">Goniasteridae</taxonomicName>
owing to its occurrence at lower bathyal and abyssal depths,&gt; 
<quantity box="[254,339,1483,1509]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" unit="m" value="1000.0">1000 m</quantity>
to 
<quantity box="[375,463,1482,1509]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.2" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" unit="m" value="5200.0">5200 m</quantity>
. Atlantic species were reviewed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Halpern, J. A." box="[863,1035,1483,1509]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" pagination="129 - 142" refId="ref46522" refString="Halpern, J. A. (1969) Biological Investigations of the deep sea. 46. The genus Litonotaster (Echinodermata, Asteroidea). Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 82, 129 - 142." type="journal article" year="1969">Halpern (1969)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Clark, A. M. &amp; Downey, M. E." box="[1089,1367,1483,1509]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" refId="ref45928" refString="Clark, A. M. &amp; Downey, M. E. (1992) Starfishes of the Atlantic. Chapman and Hall, London, 794 pp." type="book" year="1992">Clark &amp; Downey (1992)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
